 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Complaint Specialist HeartFlow, Inc. Austin, TX Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description The Complaint Specialist will play a critical role in the timely review of complaints to ensure investigations are complete and well documented, and regulatory reporting determination documentation. 
This position requires an understanding of Medical Device regulatory obligations for compliance within the scope of the department (E.g., 21 CFR 820.198, 21 CFR 803, 21 CFR 806, MEDDEV Annex 3 / Annex 4, Health Canada MPR and other global post-market regulatory obligations as required). 
 Job Responsabilities: 
Primary responsibilities include, but are not limited to identifying, reviewing, and processing complaints for evaluation as required by applicable regulations, standards, and company policy.
 Assist Customer Support and serve as a liaison for complaint escalations.
 Review of complaint investigations and trends. General understanding of CAPA, NCR, and Health Hazard Evaluation. 
 Skills Needed: 
Excellent communications, documentation and time management skills required 
Critical thinking skills and great attention to detail 
Experience with EDMS - Electronic Document Management System 
Proficient with Windows, MS Office, Excel, and PowerPoint skills 
 
 
Educational Requirements & Work Experience:
